Savage could not be reached for comment Tuesday. A message left for him at his workplace, the law firm Gideon Asen, was not immediately returned.

Blanchard, who is also known as “Corn Pop” by his thousands of [social media followers](https://x.com/pwa1776), regularly posts [videos from Maine school board meetings](https://www.centralmaine.com/2025/11/19/parents-rights-groups-backed-by-conservative-funders-bring-the-fight-to-maine-school-boards-2/), as well as inflammatory content about transgender students and school policies.

